BIS conference (International Conference on Business Information Systems) - is an annual conference for scientific discussions on the development, implementation and application of business information systems, based on innovative ideas and computational intelligence methods. The conference addresses a wide scientific community and experts involved in the development of  business computing applications. Conference is organized by the Department of Information Systems, Poznań University of Economics with local academic institutions (depending on the venue).

First BIS conference was organized in 1997 in Poznań. General Chair of the conference is Prof. Witold Abramowicz.


